proyecto_TT_nombre_proyecto: Name that the user gives to this simulation (eg apartment 01, LuzScalera01, garage00 ...)
mapa_MSG_Polygon: Define the area in which the panels will be installed. The application will close when double-click
mapa_MSG_LineString: Double-click to indicate the geographical orientation of the panels
mapa_MSG_posicionConsumo: A click to position a new consumption
mapa_TT_deshacer: Allows to cancel the last vertex created
mapa_TT_tipoMapa: Allows you to exchange between Sátelite or Map
mapa_TT_nombreBase: Identize the name of this basis for future references
mapa_TT_lonlat: It is not necessary to fill this field, it is only used to focus the map on these coordinates
mapa_TT_areaPlana: Surface measured on the map in square meters
mapa_TT_inclinacionTejado: Roof inclination, measured with respect to the horizontal of the terrain, on which the panels will be mounted
mapa_TT_areaCorregida: Real area available corrected by the roof inclination
mapa_TT_maximaPotencia: Maximum peak power to be installed in this area (see conversion parameter
mapa_TT_inclinacion: Degrees of inclination (between 0 and 90) on the roof that the panels will have. If ‘optimal’ is marked, it is not necessary to indicate any value
mapa_TT_inclinacionOptima: Mark this field if you want the system to calculate the optimal value of the panel inclination
mapa_TT_acimut: The angle between the south with the horizontal projection of the sun. If the panels were oriented to the south, the azimuth will be 0º, made the east, -90º and west 90º. This field is filled by indicating on the map the orientation that the panels will have. If it is not completed it is assumed that it is 0
mapa_TT_angulosOptimos: Mark this field if you want the system to calculate the optimal value of inclination and azimut
mapa_TT_localizar: After indicating city and direction where the panels will be installed Pulse ‘intro'
mapa_TT_candidatos: Select the correct direction or sign up on the lower map with a double mouse pulsation
mapa_MSG_territorio: The application is only valid for Spain
mapa_MSG_insular: Be careful, you are in non -peninsular territory. 3.0TD rates can be wrong (Please review).
mapa_TT_area: Button to create a new base to install panels
mapa_MSG_definePosicionMapa: You must define at least one base on the map before continuing
consumo_MSG_descripcionFuentes:
There are two ways to provide the consumer profile information
  • with a CSV file obtained from the website of your distribution company. See instructions here
  • Using the standard Ree profile according to Resolution of December 23, 2021, of the General Directorate of Energy Policy and Minesboe and the estimated annual consumption of the installation

    • you must choose one or the other according to the information you have.
consumo_TT_nombre: Identize the name of this consumption for future references
consumo_TT_csvREE: Select the source type from which the consumption profile will be loaded
consumo_TT_energiaAnualREE: In case of opting for the REE type profile, the estimated annual consumption must be indicated
consumo_TT_fuenteCSV: Identify the Consumption file downloaded from your distribution company
consumo_TT_tarifa: The type of rate hired with the commercialization company
consumo_MSG_numeroLimitadoRegistros: Notice: there are only {{registros}} records that do not complete one year of statistics
consumo_MSG_definirFicheroConsumo: You must define the consumption file before continuing
consumo_MSG_definirPotenciaBaseREE: Must define an annual base consumption greater than 0 for the REE profile
consumo_TT_descripcionTarifaP1: P1 or tip rate (the most expensive in 2.0TD)
consumo_TT_descripcionTarifaP3: P3 or Llano Rate (the cheapest in 2.0TD)
consumo_TT_valorTarifa: Indicate the price in euros without VAT of this rate
consumo_TT_valorCompensa: Indicate the price in euros without VAT with which the electricity company pays the electricity not consumed
consumo_TT_ficheroTarifas: The user can customize a file with different prices while complying with the format given in the example
parametros_LBL_kgCO2AnualPorkWh: Kg of CO2 per year per kWh
parametros_LBL_conversionAreakWp: kWp that can be installed per square meter available
parametros_LBL_descripcion: Application parameters configuration. Changes in these values ​​do not imply a recalculation of the entire set, it is necessary to return to the project tab and calculate.
tooltip_system_loss: The estimated losses of the photovoltaic system due to the deterioration of some components, adverse conditions, poor investors, etc. Can be modified in the ‘parameters’ window
tooltip_technology: The type of panel technology used in the simulation. It can be changed on the ‘parameters’ screen
main_MSG_mayorQueCero: It must be a number greater than zero

informe_MSG_procesarPrimero: You must obtain the energy balance before you can generate the report
precios_TT_gastoAnualSinPlacas: Annual electricity expenditure without solar panels. Only the variable part of the invoice is taken into account
precios_TT_gastoAnualConPlacas: The estimated annual expenditure on electricity with solar panels. Only the variable part of the invoice is taken into account
precios_TT_ahorroAnual: Annual spending difference in electricity with and without solar panels
precios_TT_noCompensadoAnual:
The amount of surplus energy that the electricity company will not compensate.
The Law (RD 244/2019) does not allow the consumer to pay any amount when the balance between the cost of the excess energy and that of the consumed of any day will be favorable to the consumer.It usually happens when more panels are installed than the advisable ones, when consumed well below the usual (on vacation) or when the compensation price of the company is high (very unlikely).
precios_TT_costeInstalacion:
Despite trying to maintain updated prices, this amount should be considered as a provisional orientation about the project that an installer can formulate (especially if it has more information about the final site).
 Some expenses are not impacting here: civil works (if necessary), insulation substitution or old tiles on the roof, elevation means if necessary, modifications that the distributor or administration could require installation and some taxes and fees that The City Council could charge (icing or works license)
precios_TT_coreccionCoste: While we try to use updated prices, the user can alter the estimation given with the value you define here. Indicate the percentage you want to increase (positive value) or decrease (negative value) the price of installation according to your particular conditions
precios_LBL_ahorroAnualPorciento: Annual savings in relation to original spending
precios_TT_IBI: Fill if the municipality where the installation is carried out bonuses the real estate tax. The Fundación Renovables facilitates a list of municipalities with bonuses in the IBI and ICO reductions.
precios_TT_subvencionIBI: The percentage with the City Council bonuses the amount of the IBI
precios_TT_duracion: The number of years during which the bonus can be applied in the IBI
precios_TT_subvencionEU: If they were to request the subsidy of the Next Generation funds, indicate whether the installation were collective (a community of owners, for example) or individual.
precios_TT_previo: The amount pending amortization at the beginning of the period
precios_TT_inversion: The amount invested during the period
precios_TT_pendiente: Pending amortization at the end of the period
precios_msg_limiteAutoconsumo: There is no EU subsidy with less than 80% of production. Current value: {{autoconsumo}}%
ayuda_TIT_localizacion: Geographical location data are identified in this tab
ayuda_TIT_consumos: In this tab, data and consumption data are identified before installation
ayuda_TIT_resultados: This tab shows the energetic balance resulting from the installation of the panels
ayuda_TIT_precios: This tab shows the economic-financial balance
ayuda_TIT_graficos: In this tab some reference graphics are shown
proyecto_TT_potenciaBase: Indicate how much electricity is consumed a year and then load. This data can be seen on the last bill
proyecto_TT_perfilREE: Red Eléctrica de España offers a very generic hourly consumption profile. Use only this option if you do not have the downloaded file from the distributor (see the guides)
app_descripcion: Here we will have fields to identify the project, including LAT-Long location that will allow us to search for the right data in PVGIS
resultados_TT_paneles: Recommended number of panels to be installed in this base. Can be modified
resultados_TT_potenciaPanel: Unitary power in KWP of the panels installed
resultados_TT_maximoHora: Maximum electricity consumption in an hour
resultados_TT_potenciaDisponible: Maximum power available at this base
resultados_TT_energiaAnual: Annual energy produced by this base
resultados_TT_energiaFaltante: Electricity that is still necessary to buy from the network after the photovoltaic installation
resultados_TT_energiaFaltante%Consumo: The percentage of the electricity bought with respect to total consumption
resultados_TT_energiaSobrante: Energy poured into the grid when production is higher than consumption
resultados_TT_energiaSobrante%Produccion: The percentage of excess electricity compared to the produced
resultados_LBL_energíaDemandadaVersusGen: Percentage of consumption with respect to production
resultados_TT_energíaDemandadaVersusGene: Percentage of consumption with respect to production. In order to opt for the subsidy of the Next Generation funds, this percentage must always be exceeding 80%
resultados_TT_energiaAhorrada: Percentage of photovoltaic energy produced with respect to the consumption
resultados_LBL_kgCO2AnualAhorradoRenovab: Kg of CO2 per year saved if renewable source
resultados_TT_kgCO2AnualAhorradoRenovabl: CO2 (kg) not expelled to the atmosphere if the origin of energy were peninsular and renewable. It can be modified in the parameter window.
resultados_LBL_kgCO2AnualAhorradoNoRenov: Kg of CO2 per year saved if non -renewable source
resultados_TT_kgCO2AnualAhorradoNoRenova: CO2 (kg) not expelled to the atmosphere if the origin of energy were peninsular and non -renewable. It can be modified in the parameter window.
resultados_TT_autoconsumoMedioAnual: Average percentage of photovoltaic energy consumed per year (not always consumed all).
resultados_TT_autosuficienciaMediaAnual: Average percentage of energy consumed from solar panels. It is a measure of independence regarding the electricity grid
resultados_TT_autosuficienciaMaxima: The maximum self -sufficiency that could be achieved if all the photovoltaic surplus could be consumed (either with batteries and/or changing consumption habits). The theoretical maximum panel number is reached when arriving in this 100%variable.
resultados_TT_rendimientoUnitario: Annual kWh that can be obtained for each KWP installed in this base
resultados_TT_maximaPotencia: It is the maximum kWp to be installed in this base depending on the available area
resultados_MSG_excesoPotencia: There is an excess of power in this base based on the available area
graficos_LBL_produccionMediaMensual: Monthly average production with {{potencia}} installed / average monthly consumption
